{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17566452","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17566452"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:41:34+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:41:34+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18829"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18829","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18829"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.02,0.01,0.94,0.02,0.01]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11562"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79590"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11562","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11562"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18829"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64894"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4989"},{"type":"tags","id":"4990"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11282"},{"type":"tags","id":"11286"},{"type":"tags","id":"11287"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27212"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27214"},{"type":"contributions","id":"45082"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79590","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/79590"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA General Practice clinic is implementing a new artificial intelligence system to assist with clinical documentation during consultations. The system can automatically generate clinical notes from recorded conversations between doctors and patients. The practice manager is eager to implement the system to improve efficiency and reduce administrative burden.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the primary ethical responsibility of healthcare practitioners when using this artificial intelligence system?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Minimising manual review of generated notes","Reducing consultation duration through automation","Maintaining ultimate responsibility for documentation accuracy","Relying exclusively on artificial intelligence transcription","Maximising the number of patients seen per day"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct answer is that practitioners must maintain \u003Cstrong\u003Eultimate responsibility for documentation accuracy\u003C/strong\u003E. While artificial intelligence tools can enhance clinical documentation, healthcare practitioners remain accountable for the accuracy and completeness of medical records, regardless of the technology used to generate them.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMinimising manual review of generated notes\u003C/strong\u003E - Human oversight of AI-generated documentation is essential to ensure accuracy and completeness\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReducing consultation duration through automation\u003C/strong\u003E - While efficiency is important, it should not compromise the quality of patient care or documentation\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERelying exclusively on artificial intelligence transcription\u003C/strong\u003E - This would be inappropriate as AI should supplement, not replace, clinical judgment in documentation\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMaximising the number of patients seen per day\u003C/strong\u003E - Patient throughput should not take precedence over maintaining accurate and complete clinical records\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHealthcare practitioners must understand the capabilities and limitations of AI documentation tools, maintain transparency with patients about their use, and ensure appropriate review and verification of all generated notes.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Healthcare practitioners remain accountable for clinical documentation even when using artificial intelligence tools for notetaking.","Informed consent and transparency about artificial intelligence use in clinical documentation is an ethical requirement.","Understanding the limitations and potential biases of artificial intelligence notetaking tools is crucial for safe clinical practice."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. New guidance on using AI in healthcare [internet]. 2024 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available from: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/News/Newsletters/September-2024.aspx#AI."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64894"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18829"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64894","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/64894"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-15T10:07:59+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-15T10:08:47+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11562"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79590"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"htt